==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-heft.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''heft'''
# {{uncountable}} [[weight]] or the [[feel]] of weight
#:''A quality hammer should have good balance and '''heft'''.''
# (''dialect &ndash; N England & Scotland'') A piece of [[mountain]] [[pasture]] to which a farm animal has become hefted. 
# An animal that has become hefted thus. 

===Transitive verb===
'''to heft''', '''hefts''', '''hefting''', '''hefted'''
#to [[lift]]; especially, to lift something [[heavy]] or feel something's weight
#:''He '''hefted''' the sack of concrete into the truck.''
# (''dialect &ndash; N England & Scotland'') the process by which a farm animal becomes accustomed to an area of mountain pasture.

